---
// Insights Preview — Latest 3 blog articles
---

<section class="insights" id="insights">
  <div class="insights-container">
    <span class="section-tag">Insights</span>

    <h2 class="insights-title fade-in">
      Wir zeigen die Arbeit.
    </h2>

    <p class="insights-subtitle fade-in">
      Technische Deep Dives, Operator-Lektionen und konträre Takes zu KI —
      inklusive was kaputtging und wie wir es gefixt haben.
    </p>

    <!-- Article Cards -->
    <div class="insights-grid">
      <!-- Article 1 -->
      <article class="insight-card fade-in">
        <div class="insight-meta">
          <span class="insight-category">MANUFACTURING AI</span>
          <time class="insight-date" datetime="2026-02-01">1. Feb 2026</time>
        </div>
        <h3 class="insight-title">
          <a href="/de/insights/cnc-planning-70-percent">
            Wie wir CNC-Planungszeit um 70% reduziert haben — und was das Projekt fast getötet hätte
          </a>
        </h3>
        <p class="insight-excerpt">
          Produktions-KI wird nicht in einem Sprint gebaut. Hier ist die Architektur, die Maschinencode mit &lt;0.2% Fehlerquoten shipped — und die drei katastrophalen Failures, die wir mit Gold reparieren mussten.
        </p>
        <div class="insight-footer">
          <span class="insight-reading-time">8 Min. Lesezeit</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Article 2 -->
      <article class="insight-card fade-in">
        <div class="insight-meta">
          <span class="insight-category">HUMAN-AI SYSTEMS</span>
          <time class="insight-date" datetime="2026-01-28">28. Jan 2026</time>
        </div>
        <h3 class="insight-title">
          <a href="/de/insights/ai-agents-cost">
            Die echten Kosten von AI Agents: Unsere Quartalszahlen
          </a>
        </h3>
        <p class="insight-excerpt">
          Jeder redet über AI Agents. Keiner zeigt die Rechnung. Hier ist, was es wirklich kostet, Mia 24/7 laufen zu lassen — API-Spend, Infrastruktur und versteckte Complexity Taxes.
        </p>
        <div class="insight-footer">
          <span class="insight-reading-time">6 Min. Lesezeit</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Article 3 -->
      <article class="insight-card fade-in">
        <div class="insight-meta">
          <span class="insight-category">CONTRARIAN TAKES</span>
          <time class="insight-date" datetime="2026-01-22">22. Jan 2026</time>
        </div>
        <h3 class="insight-title">
          <a href="/de/insights/dont-need-consultants">
            Die meisten Firmen brauchen keine KI-Berater. Hier ist, was sie stattdessen brauchen.
          </a>
        </h3>
        <p class="insight-excerpt">
          Wenn Ihre Daten nicht sauber sind, Ihr Org-Chart kaputt ist, oder Sie Hype shoppen — uns zu heuern hilft nicht. Hier ist, wann Sie NICHT anrufen sollten.
        </p>
        <div class="insight-footer">
          <span class="insight-reading-time">5 Min. Lesezeit</span>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>

    <div class="insights-cta fade-in">
      <a href="/de/insights" class="btn-secondary">
        Alle Insights lesen →
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .insights {
    padding: 8rem 2rem;
    background: var(--bg-base);
  }

  .insights-container {
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .insights-title {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 3.5vw, 2.625rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--white-pure);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .insights-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--gray-light);
    max-width: 640px;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .insights-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .insight-card {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--gray-rule);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    position: relative;
  }

  @media (hover: hover) {
    .insight-card:hover {
      border-color: rgba(200, 170, 80, 0.2);
      transform: translateY(-4px);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-card-hover);
    }
  }

  .insight-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .insight-category {
    color: var(--gold-base);
  }

  .insight-date {
    color: var(--gray-dark);
  }

  .insight-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--white-pure);
  }

  .insight-title a {
    color: inherit;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  /* Stretched link — makes entire card clickable */
  .insight-title a::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
  }

  @media (hover: hover) {
    .insight-card:hover .insight-title a {
      color: var(--gold-warm);
    }
  }

  .insight-excerpt {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--gray-light);
    line-height: 1.75;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .insight-footer {
    padding-top: 0.75rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-rule);
  }

  .insight-reading-time {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--gray-dark);
  }

  .insights-cta {
    text-align: center;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .insights-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .insights {
      padding: 5rem 1.5rem;
    }

    .insights-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Intersection Observer for fade-in
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => {
      entries.forEach(entry => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          entry.target.classList.add('visible');
        }
      });
    },
    { threshold: 0.1 }
  );

  document.querySelectorAll('.insights .fade-in').forEach(el => {
    observer.observe(el);
  });
</script>
